SENATE BILL 2015
By Kyle
HOUSE BILL 1941
By Johnson
AN ACT to amend Tennessee Code Annotated, Title 4,
Chapter 3, Part 10; Title 4, Chapter 4; Title 8; Title
9; Title 38 and Title 39, relative to state funding for
immigration and customs enforcement activities.
BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE:
SECTION 1. Tennessee Code Annotated, Title 4, Chapter 3, Part 10, is amended by
adding the following as a new section:
State funds, personnel, and other state resources shall not be obligated,
expended, or used to support any United States immigration and customs enforcement
activities in this state, including, but not limited to, conducting criminal investigations and
enforcing immigration laws.
SECTION 2. This act takes effect upon becoming a law, the public welfare requiring it.
